[61.824878, "o", "\u001b[1;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m These are reserved for block/modify/replace behavior. v1 hooks are \u001b[1;97mobserver-only\u001b[0m (return value   \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\u001b[2;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m ignored), so gating a tool call isn't supported — but you can observe \u001b[36magent.tool-use/post\u001b[0m to     \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\u001b[3;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m log/alert instead.                                                                               \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\u001b[4;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                  \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\u001b[5;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[2m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\u001b[6;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                  \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\u001b[7;1H\u001b[2K"]
[61.824892, "o", "\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97mNote:\u001b[0m Hooks live with the \u001b[1;97mcurrent project\u001b[0m (\u001b[36m.brainyard/hooks/\u001b[0m). Want me to author one? Just tell  \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\u001b[8;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m me the event, the scope (e.g. only when \u001b[36mbash\u001b[0m runs), and the side effect — I'll draft, dry-run,   \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\u001b[9;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m and register it.                                                                                 \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\u001b[10;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[92m└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\u001b[0m\u001b[11;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[12;1H\u001b[2K                                                                  \u001b[2m2 calls │ 61,457 tokens │ $0.2850\u001b[0m\u001b[13;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[14;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[1m\u001b[96m\u001b[100m❯ Create a persistent hook named audit-bash that fires after every bash tool call (the\u001b[15;1H\u001b[2K  agent"]
[61.824908, "o", ".tool-use/post event, scoped to the bash tool) and appends the command to\u001b[16;1H\u001b[2K  .brainyard/audit.log. Validate it first, then create it.\u001b[0m\u001b[17;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 1 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(30543 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(12.1s)\u001b[0m\u001b[18;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mI need the exact payload keys for agent.tool-use/post so my handler reads the bash command \u001b[0m\u001b[19;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mfrom the right place (likely :args/:command or :tool-args). I'll fetch the event catalog \u001b[0m\u001b[20;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mfirst, then validate, then create.\u001b[0m\u001b[21;1H\u001b[2K  \u001b[36m→\u001b[0m \u001b[1;36mhooks$events\u001b[0m({}): called \u001b[2m→\u001b[0m \u001b[92mdone\u001b[0m, 1ms, 3.9k chars\u001b[22;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[1;96m+\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 2 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(9.5s)\u001b[0m\u001b[23;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mI have the event catalog. For `agent.tool-use/post`, payload keys are `:agent :args \u001b[0m\u001b[24;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2m:call-id :result :tool-name` — so the bash command lives in `:args` (the bash tool's \u001b[0m\u001b[25;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2m`:args` map car"]
