[124.881656, "o", "                      \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m These are reserved for block/modify/replace behavior. v1 hooks are \u001b[1;97mobserver-only\u001b[0m (return value   \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m ignored), so gating a tool call isn't supported — but you can observe \u001b[36magent.tool-use/post\u001b[0m to     \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m log/alert instead.                                                                               \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                  \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[2m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                  \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97mNo"]
[124.881694, "o", "te:\u001b[0m Hooks live with the \u001b[1;97mcurrent project\u001b[0m (\u001b[36m.brainyard/hooks/\u001b[0m). Want me to author one? Just tell  \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m me the event, the scope (e.g. only when \u001b[36mbash\u001b[0m runs), and the side effect — I'll draft, dry-run,   \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m and register it.                                                                                 \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n                                                                  \u001b[2m2 calls │ 61,457 tokens │ $0.2850\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[96m\u001b[100m❯ Create a persistent hook named audit-bash that fires after every bash tool call (the\r\n  agent.tool-use/post event, scoped to the bash tool) and appends the command to\r\n  .brainyard/audi"]
[124.881719, "o", "t.log. Validate it first, then create it.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 1 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(30543 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(12.1s)\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mI need the exact payload keys for agent.tool-use/post so my handler reads the bash command \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mfrom the right place (likely :args/:command or :tool-args). I'll fetch the event catalog \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mfirst, then validate, then create.\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[36m→\u001b[0m \u001b[1;36mhooks$events\u001b[0m({}): called \u001b[2m→\u001b[0m \u001b[92mdone\u001b[0m, 1ms, 3.9k chars\r\n\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 2 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(32585 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(14.0s)\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mFrom hooks$events: agent.tool-use/post is non-gated/available with payload keys [:agent \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2m:args :call-id :result :tool-name]. The bash command is in (get-in event [:args \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2m:command]). I'll scope with match {:tool-name \"bash\"}, body appends the command to \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2m.brainyard/audit.log via write-file :append true. Validate with a sample eve"]
