[124.881791, "o", "           \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                 \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m Validated first (\u001b[36m:valid true\u001b[0m — all checks green, no collision), then persisted and registered.  \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                 \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97mField\u001b[0m    \u001b[2m │ \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mValue\u001b[0m                                                                               \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[2m──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m                                   \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97mid\u001b[0m       \u001b[2m │ \u001b[0m\u001b[36maudit-bash\u001b[0m                                                                          \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97mevent\u001b[0m    \u001b[2m │ \u001b[0m\u001b[36magent.t"]
[124.881807, "o", "ool-use/post\u001b[0m (non-gated, observer)                                           \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97mmatch\u001b[0m    \u001b[2m │ \u001b[0m\u001b[36m{:tool-name \"bash\"}\u001b[0m                                                                 \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97mdoc\u001b[0m      \u001b[2m │ \u001b[0mAppend every bash command to \u001b[36m.brainyard/audit.log\u001b[0m                                   \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97mpersisted\u001b[0m\u001b[2m │ \u001b[0m\u001b[36m.brainyard/hooks/audit-bash.edn\u001b[0m                                                     \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                 \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97mBody\u001b[0m reads the command at \u001b[36m(get-in event [:args :command])\u001b[0m and appends it (plus a newline) to    \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36m.brainyard/audit.log\u001b[0m via \u001b[36mwrite-file … :append true\u001b[0m.                                             \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m                                                 "]
[124.881843, "o", "                                                \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97mWhen & what it does\u001b[0m                                                                             \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m   • \u001b[1;97mFires:\u001b[0m immediately after \u001b[1;97mevery\u001b[0m \u001b[36mbash\u001b[0m tool call completes, in this project.                   \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m   • \u001b[1;97mSide effect:\u001b[0m appends the executed command to \u001b[36m.brainyard/audit.log\u001b[0m.                          \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                 \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97mNotes\u001b[0m                                                                                           \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m   • Scope is \u001b[1;97mproject-local\u001b[0m — lives with this project's \u001b[36m.brainyard/hooks/\u001b[0m and survives restarts. \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m   • Observer-only: it records the command but cannot block or alter the bash call.              \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m"]
[124.881898, "o", "\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m   • To inspect later: \u001b[36mhooks$read :id audit-bash\u001b[0m. To remove: \u001b[36mhooks$delete :id audit-bash\u001b[0m.        \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n                                                                 \u001b[2m4 calls │ 129,129 tokens │ $0.4480\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[96m\u001b[100m❯ Read back the audit-bash hook you just created and confirm it is registered and active.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 1 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(31514 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(6.7s)\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mThe user wants me to read back the audit-bash hook and confirm it's registered/active. \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mI'll call hooks$read to get its full record and hooks$list to confirm it's in the live \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mregistry. T"]
